node.text: Stay safe! Thank u for all your hard work. This will be over! Hang in there💪🏻
@natalielieew
We spoke to 2 migrant workers who are currently living at Cochrane Lodge II, a dormitory gazetted as an isolation area in Admiralty. Here’s what their experience has been like so far.

@zanmxyy yes they are humans and I also wish that we had more resources and real estate to house them properly but we make do with what we have. It's very easy to give suggestions behind a screen in your warm cozy house but it's not as simple as snap your fingers and every foreign worker has their own isolated space. There is also a possibility of spreading to the general community if we move them around too much.

@chongsterr I can confidently say that I'm not just giving suggestions from behind the screen because I'm working with my colleagues to come up with ways to help the migrant community, and I honestly don't think there is a need for anyone to comment on my personal opinion.
@zanmxyy well you can have your opinion and I can have mine as well. That's the beauty of the internet I guess.

what's the point of just isolating them but still put 12 of them in one room?? can our government do better than this? separate them up so that the cases don't increase anymore, they are humans too and they deserve the same treatment citizens get
@_rachellx_ @ryaninopoli
Good feature! thank you mothership for sharing this interview and letting us know how our migrant workers are feeling🙌🏼
12 pax in a room??! No wonder they have so many cases! I’m glad at least their food is better now!

It takes COVID-19 crisis to finally get the spotlight onto these workers, and maybe to get the smug entitled complain kings and queens of Singapore to finally not to take these workers for granted and even treat them like trash

@yunise . They are S - Pass workers. Cheap labour. What they eat and stay are all cheap. How they end up staying such a cramp place - ask our beloved MOM minister! This crisis , they will force to review their polices . Virus 🦠 stay for Long ( 5 yrs or more ) Do read on Spanish virus 🦠 in 1918. 1930 deep depression... let to a perfect storm . We are in a interesting times ahead

@yunise but who will pay for it - do we raise personal income tax and gst on the middle class, or corporate income tax and risk losing jobs, or take from the reserves? Singapore's social spending on it's citizens is alr fairly low, we willing to take the blow or not?

Singapore, we need to take care of these foreign workers. They left their homes (and loved ones) and worked hard in our country to help us build HDB, condos, offices. Just look at their accommodation, it’s sad that they can’t have private bedrooms like so many of us.

I worry about viral load of the cases from the dormitories. The infected dormitories put under lockdown but all FW are still sharing toilet and show cubicles. Whether they live in the dorms or not, they have to share same facilities, it can cause infection rate increasing dramatically.
thank you for leaving your home country to work and to built our nation. we could’ve never done this without all of you guys’ hard work. please stay safe and take care of yourself. ❤️
Can we point out how they spoke with confidence instead of thinking for too long. Man they can write a paragraph in 5 minutes while I still work on my first sentence.

Anyone who wish to donate can also go to home.org.sg 
It helps them a long way. Did mine already. Stay safe!

Thanks for this feature. So sad that they dint get the same treatment as us ( mandatory temp taking, social distance, e masks and sanitizer) earlier on and I wonder if this spread could hv prevented if they were isolated much earlier on. @mothershipsg I can't find e link in e bio to support.
Stay strong guys! We can fight over covid-19 together #sgunited
They know the severity but I CANNOT UNDERSTAND WHY SOME PEOPLE CANT😳
Please Stay healthy and safe...

From personal experience, I can vouch that these guys are the most courteous & patient people to nurse - just listen to what he said about the food given (“we have to understand about the other side too”) 👏🏽👏🏽👏🏽 Hang in there, guys. Hopefully, their living conditions will improve & stay improved even after this Pandemic dies down. 💕
I didn't expect them to get the virus.stay safe!🤞💪✊
noo :(
Something we can see and learn from them is their gratefulness, even when the food is not good, they understand the constraints of the government and did not complain.

Thank you to all the foreign workers for helping to build our nation. Do hang in there and tide though this difficult period. Our Govt and citizens have not forgotten about the hard work you all have put in building our nation with us. All your loving nature for your families and good attitude of managing yourselves and expect less in time of this crisis is what we Singaporean should salute.
... yet some people still complain have to stay at their own home 😂
Stay safe! Thank u for all your hard work. This will be over! Hang in there💪🏻
@natalielieew

owner.biography: The younger people run this account.

node.title: Migrant workers in Cochrane Lodge II talk about their isolation experience
